  ["card_enc_entry"] = {
    ["30by30"] = "The goal (also known as 30x30) set for all governments worldwide to protect 30% of land and 30 % of sea by 2030 in order to cut biodiversity loss.",
    ["Non_renewable_energy"] = "All energy resources dependent on the burning or use of limited mineral raw materials which cannot be fully recycled. These include gas, coal, oil, and also uranium.",
    ["advanced_robotics"] = "More autonomous and flexible robots (supported by AI) which may play a significant role not only in industry, but also in everyday life—deliveries, customer care, education, even elderly care. This will likely include not only drones and specialized robots, but more versatile and humanoid ones.",
    ["agroecology"] = "A method of food production that takes advantage of natural resources as effectively as possible without draining them. This leads to sustainably produced food that provides a reliable source of revenue.",
    ["agroforestry"] = "A method of farming which combines planting of trees and shrubs with crop or livestock production. It has many advantages, such as increased water retention in the landscape or resistance to extreme weather.",
    ["amazon_reforestation"] = "The regeneration of the Amazon rainforest to its original boundaries. The Amazon rainforest is essential for the generation of rainfall on the South American continent. Experts estimate that irreversible change, where the water cycle is disrupted, will occur when 20 to 25% of its total area is cut down (today, we stand at approximately 18 %). It is nessesary to reverse this trend a let the forest restore itself to its natural extents.",
    ["aquaponics"] = "A food production system that couples aquaculture (raising aquatic animals such as fish, crayfish, snails or prawns in tanks) with hydroponics (cultivating plants in water) whereby the nutrient-rich aquacultural water is used to grow plants hydroponically. ",
    ["artificial_corals"] = "Man made coral reefs used to restore and create new habitats for fish and all the other organisms that normally live in natural reefs. Natural coral reefs are threatened by changing water acidity and artifical reefs are one means of addressing this issue. However, if temperatures continue to rise, not even this technology will save marine biodiversity.",
    ["artificial_ecosystems"] = "These are artificial wetlands used to treat wastewater using plant-life and microorganisms. Specialized habitats can be created for endangered species or to restore degraded natural ecosystems. Artificial ecosystems can also improve crop yields or help run bioreactors with biofuels.",
    ["atmospheric_aerosols"] = "The spraying of atmospheric aerosols, especially sulphate aerosols, helps reflect sun rays and could help counter the effects of global warming. However, if we stopped adding aerosols to the atmosphere the planet would warm exponentially which would have a massive impact on life. The risks to human health and the environment are high - reducing the amount of incoming radiation would impact ecosystems, potentially leading to famine.",
    ["batteries"] = "Efficient energy storage technology is the key to cutting greenhouse gas emissions. Batteries are used for storing energy created by fluctuating renewables such as solar and wind power. They are also used in electric vehicles. Current lithium-ion batteries require the extraction of a substantial quantities of minerals, which is a huge risk to the environment. New technologies could bring cheaper production and better storage capacity.",
    ["biodiversity_credits"] = "Credits to be used to offset the loss of biodiversity values on sites of economic development. These credits can be traded and withdrawn. They can be created for a stewardship site via a Biodiversity Stewardship Agreement. ",
    ["biophilia"] = "A hypothesis from American biologist Edward O. Wilson, who defined being in touch with nature as a natural human need. This applies to plants in offices, houses, animals in gardens and cities etc. ",
    ["carbon_agriculture"] = "Carbon farming is a variety of agricultural methods aimed at sequestering atmospheric carbon into the soil and in crop roots, wood, and leaves. The aim of carbon farming is to increase the rate at which carbon is sequestered into soil and plant material with the goal of creating a net loss of carbon from the atmosphere.",
    ["carbon_capture"] = "The process of removing and storing atmospheric carbon. Carbon storage technology is inseparable from carbon capture technology. Its development is currently in the early stages. It is expected to be a technology which reduces the amount of CO2  in our atmosphere, rather than a definitive solution to the climate crisis.",
    ["carbon_capture2"] = "Currently, carbon is captured by chemically separating it before, during, or after burning fossil fuels. New technologies are now being tested for capturing carbon from the atmosphere directly with filters. Even if this is deployed on a large scale it will never be a magic solution to fixing climate change, it can only help if paired with the quick decarbonization of our economy.",
    ["carbon_capture3"] = "New carbon capture technologies currently developed include separation membranes, solid absorption materials, reuse processes and new materials. Ideal carbon capture solutions capture a large percentage of carbon dioxide, be low-cost, have low power consumption, be scalable, safe, and allow re-use of captured carbon as e.g., building materials.",
    ["carbon_storing_pasture"] = "A holistic system of grazing management, where pastures are managed in a way, that mimics natural grazing by herds of wild herbivores. A pattern of disturbance and regrowth leads to better plant growth, improved soil biodiversity and carbon sequestration. Shifting pastures using modern technology can make the whole proces of moving cattle much more effective.",
    ["carbon_tax"] = "A fee placed upon carbon emission producers, usually calculated as a fixed price per tonne of carbon dioxide, or other equivalent greenhouse gases, produced. This money can fund the development of renewable energy infrastructure, and other public projects.",
    ["carbon_tax_2.0"] = "There are a number of emissions trading systems in the world. In the EU, emissions trading system has set a gradually decreasing total cap of allowances, enabling companies to emit carbon dioxide. Companies must buy allowances to offset their emissions and to motivate them to modernize their infrastructure.",
    ["carbon_tax_3.0"] = "A goal and a commitment to cut greenhouse gas emissions to as close to zero as possible. Any remaining emissions should be re-absorbed from the atmosphere by oceans, forests, or carbon capture technologies.To keep global warming to less than 1.5°C (and avoid the most severe impacts of climate change) we should reach net zero by 2050.",
    ["chosen_people_left"] = "A view amongst certain entrepreneurs who invest in space travel and imagine its usefulness in their escape to a different planet. It's a plan that is economically and technologically dubious at best, while being an injustice to the rest of the population, with the damages to the environment caused by unncessary space travel. Maybe solidarity and cooperation would help humanity survive crises instead?",
    ["circular_economy"] = "This is an economic system relying on reuse of existing resources and on generating minimum waste. This system helps significantly reduce the human impact on the environment while ensuring economic sustainability.",
    ["cleaner_fossil"] = "Less harmful fossil fuels. Yes, we can use filters to capture some greenhouse gases and make coal power plants somewhat more effective. However, we are still dealing with coal, which we can only take so far, it is an inherently dirty energy source. Sooner or later we still need to transition away from fossil fuels.",
    ["coastal_bariers"] = "Infrastructure designed to protect against rising sea levels. In future, barriers will be needed to be built against more frequent flooding and storm surges. These can be artificial sand banks, sea walls, or dams. The costs will be high, but they will still be cheaper than relocating highly populated areas or dealing with the widespread destruction the flooding can cause. ",
    ["controlled_weather"] = "This is a technology designed to alter clouds and cause rain to fall earlier than it would occur under natural circumstances. This involves the seeding of clouds with chemical substances.",
    ["corals_restoration"] = "Methods for restoring corals include coral propagation (growing new corals from pieces of healthy ones and transplanting them in the ocean), construction of artificial reefs as a substrate for growth, removing dead coral and using it to rebuild damaged areas, creating protected marine areas, or cleaning water where the corals live.",
    ["decarbonisation_law"] = "These are laws and regulations to reduce carbon emissions. Having such laws and regulations is essential to motivate different actors in our economy to decrease their adverse impact on the environment.",
    ["decentralised_economy"] = "A series of local communities of producers and consumers which are preferred over large transnational companies to run the economy. A decentralised economy not only reduces the distances that goods have to travel, but also makes for a nice neighbourhood!",
    ["decentralised_power_grid"] = "The use of smaller scaled power generation. Instead of having one huge power plant to supply all households, citizens can now generate their own power and even sell overproduction to their neighbours.",
    ["deep_sea_mining"] = "The extraction of rare deposits of minerals at the bottom of the sea and oceans. With the scarcity of some rare minerals it will become more and more profitable, but it destroys marine systems and pollutes the waters.",
    ["degrowth"] = "A political, economic, and social movement claiming that wellbeing is more important than profit, thus we can use less of the world´s resources and lower our consumption, and still live happily at the same time.",
    ["desalination"] = "The removal of salt from water. A lack of drinking water is already a problem in many countries. Increasing levels of pollution and heatwaves are causing water scarcity. Desalination is an energy intensive task, but it is one of the ways to solve the problem using technology.",
    ["doughnut_economy"] = "A sustainable development framework based on respecting planetary boundaries as well as social boundaries at the same time.",
    ["eco_symbiosis"] = "Eco-symbiosis is a process where humans live in a mutually beneficial relationship with the natural environment. It might include innovations in agriculture such as agroforestry, green roofs in our cities, or use of technology that imitates or supports natural processes. In general, eco-symbiosis is the promotion of nature-based practices and reducing our environmental impact on the planet.",
    ["ecocentrism"] = "An ontological belief that denies the existence of any existential differences between man and nature. It puts man on an equal footing with other living creatures and stands in opposition to the traditional, anthropocentric concept of human superiority.",
    ["ecosystem_engineers"] = "An ecosystem engineer is any species that creates, significantly modifies, maintains, or destroys a habitat. These organisms can have a large impact on species richness and landscape-level heterogeneity of an area. As a result, ecosystem engineers are important for maintaining the health and stability of the environment",
    ["ecosystem_prioritization"] = "By protecting or actively restoring nature, we can reduce carbon emissions while generating resources for our economy in a nature-friendly way. This is because nature plays a key role in efforts to mitigate or reverse climate change.",
    ["ecosystem_restoration"] = "The process of undoing damage to natural ecosystems. Restoring nature can help return some of the most valuable ecosystems along with the valuable functions they provide. Restoring ecosystems can also help sequester some of that excess carbon dioxide. ",
    ["ecosystems_of_22th_century"] = "A hypothetical concept which envisions a \\",
    ["electric_transport"] = "Sustainable transport refers to ways of transportation that are sustainable in terms of their social and environmental impacts. Transportation sustainability is largely being measured by transportation system effectiveness and efficiency as well as the environmental and climate impacts of the system.",
    ["electric_transport_2.0"] = "Sustainable transport 2.0 is not only about technological advances, but also about a series of regulations and measures that will facilitate their everyday use. It is therefore not only about public transport with sustainable drives or autonomous or affordable electric cars, but also about their legislative support, infrastructure, shared mobility options and optimisation of cities, the so-called smart cities.",
    ["emission_clean"] = "The use of carbon capture used directly at power plants and industrial facilities. It is currently considered to be a very promising technology in reducing carbon emissions, but at the same time it is still in the early phases of development and it is very costly.",
    ["energy_efficient_cities"] = "An energy efficient city is a sustainable city, eco-city, or green city is a city designed with consideration of social, economic, and environmental pillars, and provides a habitat which protects its inhabitants from extreme weather.",
    ["fracking"] = "Fracking is a method of extracting natural gas and oil from rock formations deep underground. With this method, we can access resource deposits which were previously inaccessible. However, the negative effects on the environment, air pollution, and quality of water is huge.",
    ["fusion3_0"] = "An advanced phase in the research and implementation of fusion energy which could be used for massive energy production. The building of the first fusion power plants can be expected to be very expensive, and it will also require extensive research.",
    ["fusion_power"] = "Fusion power is a hypthetical clean energy source. Fusion power might one day be a clean source of energy able to produce energy at a scale never before seen . The first attempts to do a nuclear fusion in which we create more energy than we consume on the whole process are successfully behind us. A lot of research and resources will have to be invested into the technology, but it could become the ultimate goal of energy transformation. ",
    ["gas_power_plants"] = "These are plants that consume natural gas to generate energy. A lot of energy mixes across Europe rely on gas power plants. This is because they are very flexible as they can quickly react to any network outages, as opposed to renewable energy sources, such as solar or wind power, whose effectivity can be affected by the weather. However, f to function, they still need to burn gas, a fossil fuel, which produces emissions compable to coal.",
    ["genetical_utopia"] = "A hypothetical society in which disabilities and diseases are eliminated with the help of technology. Impacts of global environmental degradation are mitigated by genetic modifications, helping people resist heat, extreme humidity, grow gills to withstand flooding and filtration villi allowing to drink dirty water. It is not agreed upon among scientists that this is even possible or morally acceptable.",
    ["geoengineering"] = "A scheme of large-scale intervention into the Earth's natural systems which aims to counteract climate change. Besides ethical, political, and technological concerns, there is also a risk of deepening the climate crisis through unexpected side-effects.",
    ["giant_hydroplants"] = "Hydroelectric power plants share all the advantages of renewable sources of energy, just on a larger scale. However, building such a huge construction will have a significant effect on ecosystems, water flow, landscape, and animals. ",
    ["green_deserts"] = "A colossal process of returning of plants and animals to the great Sahara desert, all aided by the careful hand of the ecosystem engineer.",
    ["guerrilla_gardening"] = "Basically, planting flowers, vegetables or trees anywhere in urban areas. By anywhere we mean even places where it is not necesarilly allowed. Guerillla gardening helps to make urban areas greener, when the authorities fail to act.",
    ["habitable_planet"] = "In the past 15 years, we have found evidence of thousands of planets outside of our solar system. There could potentially be many Earth-like planets in our galaxy that could sustain human life. A second Earth would need to be the correct size, have liquid water, orbiting its star in the so called Goldilock's Zone, not too close, not too far away, just enough to support life. So far the only planet that we know for sure to be habitable is Earth.",
    ["home_wind_farms"] = "Smale scale electricity generation using wind energy on a smaller scale might provide cheap, sustainable source of electricity for smaller communities and houses. However, it still relies on wind, might be loud and visually very dominant. ",
    ["human_engineering"] = "Human engineering is the idea of implementing various technologies into humans to enhance their physical and mental capabililities. In initial stages, it could include devices improving vision or diabetes. Some more advanced versions might deal with brain-computer interfaces, or even help people adapt to new climate conditions. This area of research could improve human health but is connected to many ethical and societal issues. ",
    ["hydroenergy"] = "This is a clean and renewable source of electricity. Moreover, power plants have a relatively long lifespan reducing the need to replace them frequently. On the other hand, hydroenergy requires running source of water and there is a risk in larger constructions that it might affect the natural flow of rivers and the river biodiversity.",
    ["hydropony"] = "A technological method of growing plants, vegetables, and fruit with using a nutritional solution instead of soil.",
    ["idea_incubator"] = "This is an institute that supports ideas, smaller start-ups, NGOs and research organisations might rgenerate interesting ideas and smart ways how to solve some issues we face.",
    ["incubator"] = "One of the first organizations providing resources and support to science startups, businesses and individuals emerged in 1950s. Often tied to universities, research institutions, governments or for-profit initiatives, science incubators serve as a office space or lab space and provide equipment, mentoring and a meeting place.",
    ["industry20"] = "The 20th century saw a huge rise in production of consumer goods, construction and industry. It was mostly based on burning fossil fuels and so it created a lot of greenhouse gases that negatively impacted the climate of our planet.",
    ["industry22"] = "A novel approach to industrial resources. We still do not know whether it will be based on fusion energy, how much artificial intelligence will be involved or what new technologies we might develop, but what we know is that it should be carbon negative or at least carbon neutral. ",
    ["kelp_plantation"] = "A sustainable form of agriculture which relies on cultivation of kelp on the sea floor. The kelp is then harvested and used for example as food.",
    ["lab_food"] = "Meat and dairy products grown in laboratiories without the need to feed or harm living animals. Although far from being natural, these prefabricated foodstuffs could, in the future, help reduce the need to raise collossal numbers of cattle including the disposal of their waste.",
    ["lifestyle_changes"] = "A change in lifestye to adapt to modern conditions. Modern challenges require a modern lifestyle where our ecological footprint will not hinder our ability to live a fulfilling life in the future. Accumulating money and possessions is not the purpose of life, and environmental considerations also mean a better and healthier place to thrive.",
    ["local_solutions"] = "Solving problems a local level.Even small actions at a local level can significantly impact our climate and nature's recovery if enough people do them. Examples of this include rainwater harvesting, reintroducing natural engineers like beavers to our countryside, or changing the way we grow food. ",
    ["loss_damage"] = "Loss and damage is the harm caused by anthropogenic climate change. In the context of the UN Framework Convention on Climate Change process, it refers to the establishment of a compensation mechanisms allows the most impacted countries at least partially to cope with unexpected catastrophies.",
    ["mangroves_planting"] = "Mangroves are a group of trees and shrubs that live in coastal intertidal zones. Mangrove forests stabilize the coastline, reducing erosion from storm surges, currents, waves, and tides. The intricate root system of mangroves also makes these forests attractive to fish and other organisms seeking food and shelter from predators.",
    ["mass_airconditioning"] = "Air conditioning is a means of artificially helping people cope with excessive heat. They are effective in keeping the indoor areas habitable even during strong heatwaves, however, they use a lot of energy. As such, they contribute to the production of carbon emissions, especially in areas using mostly fossil fuels to generate electricity. ",
    ["mass_reforestation"] = "The process of replanting of large quantities of trees can remove carbon dioxide from the atmosphere. Reforestation can also help increase diversity, water management, or in the long-term provide sources of wood for the economy. However, reforestation is not only about planting trees, but also about how to take care of them until they grow. It is one of many policies that need to be combined to effectively reduce carbon emissions.",
    ["massive_automation"] = "Wide automation of manufacturing promises substantially more effective production, potentially cutting both environmental and economic costs. When paired with corresponding reforms, it might foster wider political and social transformations.",
    ["massive_extraction"] = "The removal of resources from the natural enviroment. Because our industry and new technologies require more and more mineral resources, their extraction is very often results in a big hit on the environment. ",
    ["meteo_models"] = "These are computer models that allow us to better understand climate change. Developing complex meteorological models might provide us with exact predictions of climate change impact on our planet, agriculture or even on spread of diseases. As such, these models can help to decide which preventive measures to implement to effectively mitigate the crucial impact of climate change on our society. ",
    ["miracle_enzym"] = "A miracle enzyme was not yet discovered. In the context of the environmental crisis this would be an enzyme which could absorb CO2 from the air, or which would be able to produce a sufficent amount of clean energy. The closest thing to this is the enzyme HUC which can produce clean energy from atmospheric hydrogen, but in very small quantities. The research is still in early stages.",
    ["modified_babies"] = "A modification of the DNA of the human embryo with the intention of curing a specific medical condition.This is still highly controversial and it could also lead to unexpected genetic complications for future generations, not to mention social inequalities based on gene-discrimination.",
    ["modular_fusion_reactors"] = "The technology of fusion reactors is still in it's infancy so modular fusion reactors are far in the future as of now. However, their potential impact on the energy sector could be tremendous as they would be a scalable, stable, and sustainable source of energy.",
    ["modular_nuclear_reactor"] = "Smaller nuclear reactors might solve one the current largest issues of  nuclear energy—its cost. Building and maintaning the safe nuclear power plant is very expensive compared to alternatives, building it on smaller local scales might solve the issue.",
    ["moon_commuting"] = "The hypothectial concept of routine travel to the moon.We are currently technologically very far from from any permanent settlement on different planets. Therfore, our moon might be the least challenging destination due to the distance and its conditions. Thus, a settlement on the moon might represent a first step in a very long-term goal of human habitation on other planets. This objective would require a tremendous amount of effort and resources. ",
    ["more_coal"] = "Coal energy, was the backbone of the industrial revolution. It is very cheap, but it emits vast quantities of emissions. As long as we stick to this source, it will be very hard to face the environmental crisis.   ",
    ["natural_hedges"] = "A hedge is a line of closely spaced shrubs or trees, planted form a barrier or mark the boundary of an area. Hedges are recognised as part of a the cultural heritage of many countries for their great value to wildlife and the landscape. Increasingly, they are also valued for the major role they play in preventing soil loss and reducing pollution, and for their potential to regulate water supply and reduce flooding.",
    ["nature_conservation"] = "Nature conservation is both a moral philosophy and a conservation movement focused on protecting biodiversity. Its premise is that human influence can only be detrimental to nature and it seeks ways to extract the human presence from ecosystems. ",
    ["net_zero"] = "This refers to a point, where together we begin removing carbon dioxide from the atmosphere rather than adding it.\\nThere ways to achieve this including direct carbon capture technologies, and restoring ecosystems and marine habitats.",
    ["no_limit_drilling"] = "Is the practice of mining resources until exhaustion. Unmined deposits of rare minerals are often situated under the unique ecosystems. If wedecide to ignore these often well-protected areas, we will gain access to yet unexploited rare minerals, but we may destroy unique ecosystems in the process.",
    ["no_tech_civilisation"] = "A society without any technology would significantly reduce the living standards we are accustomed to. Long-distance travel, medical care, communication technologies, and modern agriculture would completely dissapear. However, it isn't clear whether renouncing all technology would even solve the climate crisis, as we would not develop further any scientific understanding helping to decrease the damage that is already done.",
    ["nuclear2_0"] = "Nuclear 2.0 reactors are a new generation of nuclear reactors. They are more durable, more efficient and with a better ratio between their construction cost and electricity produced. They also produce less radioactive waste. A number of technologies that can further improve the functionality of nuclear power plants are under development.",
    ["nuclear_energy"] = "The generation of electricity from nuclear power sources. It takes a lot of time and resources to build a nuclear power plant, however, once buillt, nuclear power is a stable source of energy with relatively mediocre carbon footprint. Furthremore, safety remains a concern as there have been multiple accidents in the past and it is probable that more will occur.",
    ["nuclear_safe"] = "These are modern nuclear 2.0 reactors with enhanced safety through a range of instruments and regulations. There are regular inspections, mandatory implementation of comprehensive safety and control systems, reactors are built to high safety standards and regularly maintained and inspected by independent authorities. All these mechanisms significantly reduce the risk of a nuclear disaster, but their implementation continues to raise the cost of building and maintaining nuclear power plants.",
    ["offshore_wind_farms"] = "This is the practice of placing wind turbines in littoral areas. Installing wind turbines near the shore has multiple advantages, such as consistently higher wind speeds and less impact on people and the landscape. They might be more expensive to build and maintain, but those costs are fast decreasing with wider adoption. ",
    ["permaculture"] = "A portmanteau of the words permanent and culture. Permaculture refers to the philosophy and techniques of using natures proceses and designs to shape landscapes, produce food and organize society.",
    ["planet_b_colonised"] = "Even though promoted for example by a renowned physicist Stephen Hawking, the dream of colonizing another planet as a failsafe for earthly catastrophe has many practical issues. These include economic costs, inhospitable environment of other planets (such as Mars) and impracticality of transporting billions of humans. It remains a fantasy with considerable downsides.",
    ["planetary_thermostat"] = "The invention of the so called planetary thermostat would involve the implementation of an array of different geoengeneering solutions which would allow humans to control and change the Earth's climate. It isn't clear what specific technologies we would need to develop to make it work reliably. At the same time, it's uncertain if this vision is feasible considering the fragility of the Earth's ecosystem.",
    ["pollution_regulations"] = "A type of legislation that might easily compell energy and industry producers to implement greater limits on how much they pollute the environment. Such legislation would make production more expensive and would undoubtably lead to pressure from lobbyists groups to maintain the status quo.",
    ["precision_agriculture"] = "Precision agriculture is a farming branch based on machine-precise sowing and application of agro-chemicals, using technologies such as homing with satelites or measuring with drones. It is used in both crop and livestock production. Precision agriculture often employs technologies to automate agricultural operations, improving diagnosis, decision-making, and performance. ",
    ["protected_landscapes"] = "Protected landscapes are areas like national parks or nature reserves that are protected from human activities that might damage the natural resources within. To some extent, they can help with storing carbon emissions, but mostly they protect the biodiversity. ",
    ["radiative_cooling"] = "Special materials, coatings and foils which help achieve the effect of radiative cooling by radiating absorbed heat into space at specific wavelengths. Mass use of this technology could bring worldwide decrease in temperatures. However, the realization of this concept would be costly, and with uncertain outcomes.",
    ["rage_againts_machines"] = "Humanity has a history of directing their economic and social anger against technology. The most notable are the luddites, who in 19th century England protested industrialization and the replacement of manual labor by machines. Today, sometimes called neo-luddism, it means people opposing the automation, emphasizing their presumed effects on labor rights and employment.",
    ["rainwater_harvest"] = "Rainwater harvesting is the collection and storage of rain, rather than allowing it to run off. Rainwater is collected from roof-like surfaces and redirected to a tank, cistern, deep pit (well, shaft, or borehole), aquifer, or a reservoir with percolation, so that it seeps into the ground and replenishes the ground water",
    ["reflective_sheets"] = "Also called \\",
    ["refugee_integration"] = "Is the process of absorbing refugees into new communities. A climate change already significantly affects our planet, many places are becoming almost uninhabitable. Therefore, a lot of people are forced to move. Investing resources to help them settle in and get a fresh start might help prevent conflicts and in the end could benefit the economy as well.",
    ["regenerative_agriculture"] = "Regenerative agriculture is a conservation and rehabilitation approach to food and farming systems. Practices include recycling as much farm waste as possible and adding composted material from sources outside the farm. As soil health improves, input requirements decrease, crop yields and soils become more resilient against extreme weather and harbor fewer pests and pathogens",
    ["renewable_energy"] = "Renewable energy is a relatively cheap source of power. It can be a small solar or wind power plant, or it can be a larger project. However, despite all its advantages, it is important to keep in mind that renewable eneregy relies heavily on the weather and we often need precious minerals to build them.",
    ["research centers"] = "Research centers and institutions are essential to our understanding of climate change and how we deal with its consequences. Solutions might focus on a broad range of areas, including the ways how to adapt to climate change, geoengineering, climate modeling or preparations for the impact of climate change on human society and economy.",
    ["resistant_crops"] = "Genetically modified crops whose traits can address agricultural challenges and, while doing so, help slow climate change. Herbicide-resistant crops do not die or wilt when they’re treated with herbicides that kill unwanted vegetation. Crops can also be genetically engineered to resist harmful insects by incorporating a protein from insect-killing bacteria. ",
    ["robobees"] = "Robobees or artificial bees, are small robots that mimick the behavior of bees in pollinating flowers. Robobees are currently an experimental concept with no guarantee of success. They might be one of the ways to solve the sharp decline of bee populations. However, from today's perspective, it seems that it might be significantly easier to protect existing pollinators populations or manually pollinate plants.",
    ["safer_nuclear"] = "Today, modern nuclear power plants are secured by a number of instruments and regulations. Comprehensive safety and control systems are mandatorily implemented, reactors are built to high safety standards and regularly maintained and inspected by independent authorities. All these mechanisms significantly reduce the risk of a nuclear disaster, but their implementation continues to raise the cost of building and maintaining nuclear power plants.",
    ["safer_nuclear2_0"] = "Safe Nuclear Reactors 2.0 are a new, more robust and efficient generation of nuclear reactors with enhanced security. There are regular inspections, mandatory implementation of comprehensive safety and control systems, reactors are built to high safety standards and regularly maintained and inspected by independent authorities. All these mechanisms significantly reduce the risk of a nuclear disaster, but their implementation continues to raise the cost of building and maintaining nuclear power plants.",
    ["sahara_solar_field"] = "An ambitious project to build a huge field of solar panels in the Sahara desert. Covering just a small percentage of the desert would harness enough energy to power the whole world. However the construction would be very challenging and expensive and transmitting the power across the world would be difficult. Covering more than a small percentage of the desert would also impact the world climate in unpredictable ways.\\n\\n\\n",
    ["science_funding"] = "This is the process of obtaining funds for science projects. Investing sufficient resources in scientific research and capacity can be crucial to ensuring that our knowledge and technologies have a chance to counter the effects of climate change on our planet. Several promising technologies are being developed, but science alone may not be enough to avert climate change unless action is taken in other sectors.",
    ["smog_sucking_vacuum"] = "This a technology that attempts to filter smog from the air. New technologies help capture carbon dioxide emissions and therefore reduce the excessive release of this greenhouse gas into the atmosphere. However, the high cost of carbon capture remains a significant barrier to widespread adoption.",
    ["societal_change"] = "This is the process of changing a way of life at a societal level. All the changes in economy and the way we think about our planet relies on people and their ideas. Set priorities of the societal system that we create, define how will our world look like in the future. ",
    ["solar_energy"] = "This is an easy to implement and well-known type of renewable energy. The newest types of solar panels are very effective with long service life. They can be easily installed on roofs of public and private buildings.",
    ["solar_energy_2.0"] = "In solar energy, the main changes are new materials increasing effectivity and durability, machine learning which might help to predict electric network demands and better batteries which can offset inconsistent energy load in the grid.",
    ["solar_subsidies"] = "Majority of countries provide financial incentives for individuals and businesses to install solar panels, including feed-in tarrifs for generating and feeding the power into the grid as well as grants and loans.",
    ["space_mirrors"] = "Space mirrors is an object, or a group of objects, placed in space with the aim of reducing the amount of sun rays that reach the Earth's surface and thus reduce its temperature. The concept of space mirrors is known but it still isn't clear whether it's practically feasible. It would definitely be very expensive, and carry high risks for our ecosystem.",
    ["space_research"] = "Space research is the branch of scientific enquiry that pushes the boundaries of human knowledge in relation to space. Travelling to neigbouring planets is one thing, but sustaining any long-term population there is still far from our current reality. Extreme quantities of resources would have to be invested into development of new technologies, discovering new potentially habitable planets and their terraforming. ",
    ["therma_drill"] = "Geothermal power is the electrical power generated from heat emanating from the Earths internal processes.",
    ["transition_from_fossils"] = "Transition from fossils is a theme in regulations and policies that seeks to move beyond harmful fossil fuel consumption. Measures include incentives for buyng electric vehicles, emission standards, support of renewable energy or carbon pricing. In general, all these measures are designed to support usage of cleaner forms of energy.",
    ["tribal_culture"] = "Tribal culture is a term that refers to the reordering of our society when we decide to globally move away from technology and return to a simpler way of life.",
    ["voluntary_modesty"] = "This is an effective solution to environmental problems which calls changes in levels of consumption. Sociologists have described moderation in households of high socio-economic status in affluent countries, and also a type of modesty which cannot be a response to the experience of abundance. Sustainable living based on self-restraint could be considered to be a symptom of the summit of cultural evolution to date.",
    ["vr_fully_utopia"] = "A society in which every person \\",
    ["vr_worlds"] = "These are virtual reality environments created digitally. VR technology can be useful in many ways in the fight against climate change. It can save costs when travelling, but beyond that it has the ambition to streamline the way we work and interact with one another. ",
    ["wave_hydro_plants"] = "These are a promising new techonology for generating renewable electricity from ocean waves.\\nIn comparison to giant hydroplants, the impact of wave hydro plants construction on the ecosystems is much smaller. In the right location, they couldprovide a stable source of electricity, but they are technically challenging to build.",
    ["wind_energy"] = "Wind energy is the gerneration of power from wind. It is one of the main sources of renewable energy; it is functional even during the night. It is relatively cheap. However, to fully profit from its potential, energy storage systems are essential.",
    ["wind_energy_2.0"] = "These are more advanced technologies that enable more efficient generation and use of wind energy may include the downwind turbine rotation optimalisation by means of AI, using more reliable and efficient materials, experimenting with vertically oriented turbines, or a range of other lesser-known solutions.",
    ["world_climate_fund"] = "Historically the largest fund for the restoration of the most valuable ecosystems. States, companies, and the richest individuals send huge sums of money to be spent on restoring and protecting the richest biomes.",
  },
