    ["climate_change_text"] = "Climate change refers to the long-term warming of the planet caused by the increasing levels of greenhouse gases in the atmosphere. These gases, such as carbon dioxide, methane, and water vapor, trap heat from the sun and prevent it from being released back into space, leading to an overall warming of the Earth's surface.\\n\\n\\nHuman activities, such as the burning of fossil fuels, deforestation, and agriculture, are the main sources of the increased levels of greenhouse gases in the atmosphere. As the planet warms, it can lead to a range of impacts, including more frequent and severe heatwaves, droughts, and storms, as well as rising sea levels and disruptions to ecosystems. These impacts can have serious consequences for human health, agriculture, and the environment. It is important to take action to reduce greenhouse gas emissions and mitigate the impacts of climate change.",
